author: Nikhil Lohade
title: East African Country Seizes Strategic DP World Container Terminal
text:
The East African nation of Djibouti on Friday seized a container terminal run by one of the worldâ€™s largest port operators, as the tiny country seeks to exploit a contest among Middle Eastern rivals to control a region of growing geopolitical and commercial importance.

Djibouti, a country the size of Massachusetts located at where the Red Sea and the Gulf of Aden meet, took over the Doraleh Container Terminal from Dubai-based DP World, which owns a 33% stake in the port. Now, some expect Djibouti, which owns the rest of the...
